Source:  Edmonds Cookery Book
Author:
Vol / Page:  35
Edition:
Quote:  Mock Cream... Mix cornflour and milk together smoothly, boil for 3 or 4 minutes. Mix butter and sugar to a cream, add cooked cornflour when cold, beat well. Mock Cream Filling 3 oz. butter, 2 oz. flour, 2 oz. sugar, teaspoon gelatine softened in 1 tablespoon cold water.., 2 tablespoons boiling water.
Notes:

Date:  12/7/1986
Source:  Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page:  52
Edition:
Quote:  As far as I know, 'mock cream' cake fillings are indigenous to this country., There are no similar recipes in any of the English, Continental or American cook-books. Why we needed to invent imitation cream when there was always so much of the real thing around is a mystery to me.
